[SN]TITLE[SN]
Painted doors art project opens in Aberdeen

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Doors in Aberdeen are being transformed as part of a new art project.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Artists are taking part in the painted doors Aberdeen Inspired initiative with the aim of brightening up the city.
Painter and glassmaker Shelagh Swanson opened the project in Windmill Brae. Langstane Place, The Green and Correction Wynd will also feature.
Aberdeen Inspired chief executive Adrian Watson said: "Our Summer of Art campaign is about making art and culture accessible to all."
